    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-05-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-05-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="282"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d282">
                <head>No. 14.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Affidavit of Charles B. Wilson.</hi>
                </head>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Honolulu, Oahu</hi>,<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Hawaiian Islands, ss.</hi>
                </p>
                <p>And now comes Chas. B. Wilson of Honolulu, aforesaid, and upon oath deposes and
                    says:</p>
                <p>That on the 17th day of January, A. D. 1893, between the hours of 7 and 8 p.m. of
                    that day, he surrendered, by order of the Queen and Cabinet to Jno. J. Soper, as
                    commander-in-chief of the forces of the Provisional Government, and representing
                    that Government, the police station with all the arms and munitions of war, the
                    control of the police force and Oahu jail, together with all Government property
                    under his control as marshal of the Kingdom.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Chas. B. Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">Sworn and subscribed before me <date
                            calendar="gregorian" when="1893-05-06">this 6th day of May, A. D.
                            1893</date>.</dateline>
                    <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">P. J. Testa</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Notary Public, First Judicial Circuit.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
